1.
The main difference between System Call and Library Call is
that System call is a request to the kernel to access a
resource while library call is a request to use a function
defined in a programming library. The operating system
is an interface that allows the application programs to
access hardware resources.

2. file permissions : rw- rw- r--
   umask :               r--  -w- rwx
   -----------------------------------------
   result : -wx r-x ---




